@namespace TheCanalaveLibrary.SharedUI

@* Universal rich-text *editing* composite (third-party wrapper around Blazored TextEditor / Quill.js,
   spec §5.30.2). Sibling to the RichTextView leaf in this same cross-cutting cluster — no single
   feature owns either; the cluster's feature is "rich-text rendering/editing" (SKILL.md Code
   Organization). Consumed by Chapters, Comments, Recommendations, BlogPosts, Profiles, Messaging.

   Device axis (spec §5.30.2: desktop full toolbar / mobile compact toolbar) is handled the same way
   the rest of the codebase handles structurally-different desktop/mobile content — separate
   compositions (layer4-style.md Responsive Breakpoints: "when desktop and mobile are structurally
   different, use separate components instead"), not a runtime toggle inside this one component. A
   `Compact`-boolean variant was tried and discarded: toggling it at runtime doesn't work cleanly
   anyway (Quill binds toolbar listeners once, at construction — a later RenderFragment change doesn't
   retroactively rewire it) and it fights the device-dispatch pattern used everywhere else. **MVP ships
   the desktop toolbar only; a mobile-compact variant is deferred** (not MVP-blocking — see
   workplan.md WU6 Stage note). When it's built, it'll be a separate composition this component is
   embedded in, mirroring HomeDesktop/HomeMobile, StoryDesktop/StoryMobile.

   Produces raw HTML only — never sanitizes its own output. Sanitization happens once, server-side, in
   the write service before persisting (layer2-services.md "User HTML Is Sanitized Once, On Save" and
   "The allow-list is the inverse of the toolbar" — IHtmlSanitizationService's allow-list is the mirror
   of the toolbar buttons below; extend both together).

   Quill stays mounted continuously — preview is an overlay popup on top, not a swap of the editor out
   of the tree. An in-place swap reflows the surrounding page every toggle (confusing — things move
   around); keeping Quill mounted also preserves cursor/scroll position across preview toggles. The
   overlay renders RichTextView directly so what the author sees in preview is exactly what readers see
   (spec §5.30.2).

   Inline Pokémon-sprite Quill blot is explicitly out of scope (spec §5.30.2 flags it as its own
   non-trivial task) — deferred to a future work-unit. The overlay below is a self-contained popup, not
   a pull from the (unbuilt) ConfirmDialog atom — it isn't a confirm/cancel flow, and depending on an
   unbuilt WU9 would block this work-unit; a shared modal/overlay composite may emerge later if more
   consumers need one (layer4-style.md Pattern Accumulation is where that gets recorded if it does). *@

<BlazoredTextEditor @ref="_quill" Placeholder="@Placeholder" EditorCssStyle="@FontStyle">
    <ToolbarContent>
        <span class="ql-formats">
            <select class="ql-header">
                <option selected=""></option>
                <option value="2"></option>
                <option value="3"></option>
            </select>
        </span>
        <span class="ql-formats">
            <button class="ql-bold"></button>
            <button class="ql-italic"></button>
            <button class="ql-underline"></button>
            <button class="ql-strike"></button>
        </span>
        <span class="ql-formats">
            <button class="ql-blockquote"></button>
        </span>
        <span class="ql-formats">
            <button class="ql-list" value="ordered"></button>
            <button class="ql-list" value="bullet"></button>
        </span>
        <span class="ql-formats">
            <button class="ql-link"></button>
        </span>
        <span class="ql-formats">
            <button class="ql-clean"></button>
        </span>
    </ToolbarContent>
    <EditorContent>@((MarkupString)(Html ?? string.Empty))</EditorContent>
</BlazoredTextEditor>

<button type="button" class="mt-2 rounded-md bg-primary px-3 py-1 text-white transition-colors hover:bg-primary-strong"
        @onclick="OpenPreview">
    Preview
</button>

@if (_isPreviewMode)
{
    <div class="fixed inset-0 z-50 flex items-center justify-center bg-black/50 p-4" @onclick="ClosePreview">
        <div class="max-h-full max-w-2xl overflow-y-auto rounded-xl bg-surface p-6 shadow-lg" @onclick:stopPropagation="true">
            <RichTextView HtmlContent="@_previewHtml" />
            <button type="button" class="mt-4 rounded-md bg-primary px-3 py-1 text-white transition-colors hover:bg-primary-strong"
                    @onclick="ClosePreview">
                Close
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>
}

@code {
    [Parameter] public string? Html { get; set; }

    [Parameter] public string Placeholder { get; set; } = "Write something...";

    [CascadingParameter] public ReaderDisplaySettings? Display { get; set; }

    private BlazoredTextEditor? _quill;
    private bool _isPreviewMode;
    private string? _previewHtml;

    // Mirrors RichTextView's typography (layer4-style.md "Reader Settings as CSS") so the editing
    // surface matches what preview/reading will look like. Width/justify stay structural — the
    // composing context's job, not this leaf-level concern — only the font-scope properties cross
    // the boundary here, per layer4-style.md "Tailwind's font tokens stop at RichTextView/EditorView".
    private string FontStyle =>
        $"font-family: {Display?.FontName ?? "Georgia"}; font-size: {Display?.FontSize ?? 16}px; " +
        $"line-height: {Display?.LineHeight ?? 1.5f};";

    /// <summary>
    /// Pulls the currently edited HTML. No change event exists on Blazored TextEditor, so consuming
    /// forms call this via @ref at submit time (pull-on-submit, not push-on-change). The write service
    /// sanitizes whatever this returns before persisting — this component never does.
    /// </summary>
    public async Task<string> GetHtmlAsync() => await _quill!.GetHTML();

    private async Task OpenPreview()
    {
        _previewHtml = await _quill!.GetHTML();
        _isPreviewMode = true;
    }

    private void ClosePreview() => _isPreviewMode = false;
}
